rComments: Approachable and funny prof. If you do not have some experience in socio or philosophy, this course (which is mandatory for music majors) may be difficult. The journal articles assigned are of this sort. Would also recommend taking music history courses, so you can approach his arguments (which seem to be against it) better.

Alan Stanbridge is a very nice professor, who is extremely passionate about his work. He assigns at least three readings a week for this class, and two movies that you have to watch on your own time. I've learned to read what you need to for assignments and not bother with the rest, because the work load is unrealistic to keep up with.

rComments: the man assigned at least FOUR of his own (rather mediocre) papers as required readings for the class. that clearly says something about his arrogance. also, he is the slowest marker i've ever encountered in my entire academic career. by the time we reached the end of the course, he had handed back all of ONE graded assignment. one word: lazy.
